cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PL

This paper proposes a neural network prefetcher that dynamically adapts to arbitrary memory access patterns using machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories:

- cs.AR (Computer Architecture and Embedded Systems): This sub-category covers research on computer architecture, including memory systems, cache hierarchies, and prefetching techniques.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers research on machine learning and neural networks, which are the main techniques used in the proposed prefetcher.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): This sub-category covers research on parallel computing and high-performance computing, which are relevant to the evaluation of the proposed prefetcher.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): This sub-category covers research on control systems and optimization, which are relevant to the optimization of the proposed prefetcher.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): This sub-category covers research on programming languages and compilers, which are relevant to the implementation of the proposed prefetcher.
